channelNumber.!doc: The AdSense For Content channel number for tracking the performance of this AdUnit. It must be stored as a string as it will typically be a large UINT64. (Optional)

format.!doc: the Format of the AdUnit. See https://google.com/adsense/adformats. (Optional)

map.!doc: The map associated with this AdUnit. Ads will be targeted to the location the map's viewport. (Required)

position.!doc: The position of the AdUnit. If specified, the AdUnit will be displayed at this position. Otherwise, it will not be added to the map. (Optional)

publisherId.!doc: Your AdSense for Content publisher ID. Required and must be set at the time of initialization. (Required)

iosDeepLinkId.!doc: The iOS deep link to associate with this place when a user saves the place. When the user views the place in an iOS app, this URL will serve as the link on the source string. If there is no deep link or the app that handles the deep link is not present, the webURL will be used instead.

source.!doc: The source (origin) to associate with this place when it is saved by a user. For example, this could be the name of your website or application. The user who saved the place will see this source when they view the place in Google Maps. source is required for an Attribution to be considered valid. If it is not provided an error will be thrown.

webUrl.!doc: The URL (http or https) of the page to associate with this place when a user saves the place. When the user views the place in a desktop or Android app, this URL will serve as the link on the source string. When the user views the place in an iOS app, and there is no deep link provided or the app that handles the deep link is not present, this URL will serve as the link on the source string.

bounds.!doc: The area in which to search for places. Results are biased towards, but not restricted to, places contained within these bounds.

componentRestrictions.!doc: The component restrictions. Component restrictions are used to restrict predictions to only those within the parent component. E.g., the country.

types.!doc: The types of predictions to be returned. Four types are supported: 'establishment' for businesses, 'geocode' for addresses, '(regions)' for administrative regions and  '(cities)' for localities. If nothing is specified, all types are returned. In general only a single type is allowed. The exception is that you can safely mix the 'geocode' and 'establishment' types, but note that this will have the same effect as specifying no types.

description.!doc: This is the unformatted version of the query suggested by the Places service.

matched_substrings.!doc: A set of substrings in the place's description that match elements in the user's input, suitable for use in highlighting those substrings. Each substring is identified by an offset and a length, expressed in unicode characters.

place_id.!doc: A place ID that can be used to retrieve details about this place using the place details service (see  PlacesService.getDetails()).

terms.!doc: Information about individual terms in the above description, from most to least specific. For example, "Taco Bell", "Willitis", and "CA".

types.!doc: An array of types that the prediction belongs to, for example 'establishment' or 'geocode'.

bounds.!doc: Bounds for prediction biasing. Predictions will be biased towards, but not restricted to, the given bounds. Both location and radius will be ignored if bounds is set.

componentRestrictions.!doc: The component restrictions. Component restrictions are used to restrict predictions to only those within the parent component. E.g., the country.

location.!doc: Location for prediction biasing. Predictions will be biased towards the given location and radius. Alternatively, bounds can be used.

offset.!doc: The character position in the input term at which the service uses text for predictions (the position of the cursor in the input field).

radius.!doc: The radius of the area used for prediction biasing. The radius is specified in meters, and must always be accompanied by a location property. Alternatively, bounds can be used.

types.!doc: The types of predictions to be returned. Four types are supported: 'establishment' for businesses, 'geocode' for addresses, '(regions)' for administrative regions and  '(cities)' for localities. If nothing is specified, all types are returned.

clickable.!doc: Indicates whether this Circle handles mouse events. Defaults to true.

draggable.!doc: If set to true, the user can drag this circle over the map. Defaults to false.

editable.!doc: If set to true, the user can edit this circle by dragging the control points shown at the center and around the circumference of the circle. Defaults to false.

fillColor.!doc: The fill color. All CSS3 colors are supported except for extended named colors.

map.!doc: Map on which to display Circle.

radius.!doc: The radius in meters on the Earth's surface

strokeColor.!doc: The stroke color. All CSS3 colors are supported except for extended named colors.

strokePosition.!doc: The stroke position. Defaults to CENTER. This property is not supported on Internet Explorer 8 and earlier.

visible.!doc: Whether this circle is visible on the map. Defaults to true.

zIndex.!doc: The zIndex compared to other polys.

country.!doc: Restricts predictions to the specified country (ISO 3166-1 Alpha-2 country code, case insensitive). E.g., us, br, au.

feature.!doc: The feature that was added to the FeatureCollection.

map.!doc: Map on which to display the features in the collection.

style.!doc: Style for all features in the collection. For more details, see the setStyle() method above.

geometry.!doc: The feature geometry. If none is specified when a feature is constructed, the feature's geometry will be null. If a LatLng object or LatLngLiteral is given, this will be converted to a Data.Point geometry.

id.!doc: Feature ID is optional. If provided, it can be used to look up the feature in a Data object using the getFeatureById() method. Note that a feature's ID cannot be subsequently changed.

properties.!doc: The feature properties. This is an arbitrary mapping of property names to values.

idPropertyName.!doc: The name of the Feature property to use as the feature ID. If not specified, the GeoJSON Feature id will be used.

feature.!doc: The feature which generated the mouse event.
The feature that was removed from the FeatureCollection.
The feature whose property was removed.
The feature whose geometry was set.
The feature whose property was set.

oldValue.!doc: The previous value. Will be undefined if the property was added.

clickable.!doc: If true, the marker receives mouse and touch events. Default value is true.

cursor.!doc: Mouse cursor to show on hover. Only applies to point geometries.

fillColor.!doc: The fill color. All CSS3 colors are supported except for extended named colors. Only applies to polygon geometries.

fillOpacity.!doc: The fill opacity between 0.0 and 1.0. Only applies to polygon geometries.

icon.!doc: Icon for the foreground. If a string is provided, it is treated as though it were an Icon with the string as url. Only applies to point geometries.

shape.!doc: Defines the image map used for hit detection. Only applies to point geometries.

strokeColor.!doc: The stroke color. All CSS3 colors are supported except for extended named colors. Only applies to line and polygon geometries.

strokeOpacity.!doc: The stroke opacity between 0.0 and 1.0. Only applies to line and polygon geometries.

strokeWeight.!doc: The stroke width in pixels. Only applies to line and polygon geometries.

title.!doc: Rollover text. Only applies to point geometries.

visible.!doc: Whether the feature is visible. Defaults to true.

zIndex.!doc: All features are displayed on the map in order of their zIndex, with higher values displaying in front of features with lower values. Markers are always displayed in front of line-strings and polygons.

arrival_time.!doc: An estimated arrival time for this leg. Only applicable for TRANSIT requests.

departure_time.!doc: An estimated departure time for this leg. Only applicable for TRANSIT requests.

distance.!doc: The total distance covered by this leg. This property may be undefined as the distance may be unknown.

duration.!doc: The total duration of this leg. This property may be undefined as the duration may be unknown.

duration_in_traffic.!doc: The total duration of this leg, taking into account current traffic conditions. This property may be undefined as the duration may be unknown. Only available to Maps API for Work customers when durationInTraffic is set to true when making the request.

end_address.!doc: The address of the destination of this leg.

end_location.!doc: The DirectionsService calculates directions between locations by using the nearest transportation option (usually a road) at the start and end locations. end_location indicates the actual geocoded destination, which may be different than the end_location of the last step if, for example, the road is not near the destination of this leg.

start_address.!doc: The address of the origin of this leg.

start_location.!doc: The DirectionsService calculates directions between locations by using the nearest transportation option (usually a road) at the start and end locations. start_location indicates the actual geocoded origin, which may be different than the start_location of the first step if, for example, the road is not near the origin of this leg.

steps.!doc: An array of DirectionsSteps, each of which contains information about the individual steps in this leg.

via_waypoints.!doc: An array of waypoints along this leg that were not specified in the original request, either as a result of a user dragging the polyline or selecting an alternate route.

directions.!doc: The directions to display on the map and/or in a <div> panel, retrieved as a DirectionsResult object from DirectionsService.

draggable.!doc: If true, allows the user to drag and modify the paths of routes rendered by this DirectionsRenderer.

hideRouteList.!doc: This property indicates whether the renderer should provide UI to select amongst alternative routes. By default, this flag is false and a user-selectable list of routes will be shown in the directions' associated panel. To hide that list, set hideRouteList to true.

infoWindow.!doc: The InfoWindow in which to render text information when a marker is clicked. Existing info window content will be overwritten and its position moved. If no info window is specified, the DirectionsRenderer will create and use its own info window. This property will be ignored if suppressInfoWindows is set to true.

map.!doc: Map on which to display the directions.

markerOptions.!doc: Options for the markers. All markers rendered by the DirectionsRenderer will use these options.

panel.!doc: The <div> in which to display the directions steps.

polylineOptions.!doc: Options for the polylines. All polylines rendered by the DirectionsRenderer will use these options.

preserveViewport.!doc: By default, the input map is centered and zoomed to the bounding box of this set of directions. If this option is set to true, the viewport is left unchanged, unless the map's center and zoom were never set.

routeIndex.!doc: The index of the route within the DirectionsResult object. The default value is 0.

suppressBicyclingLayer.!doc: Suppress the rendering of the BicyclingLayer when bicycling directions are requested.

suppressInfoWindows.!doc: Suppress the rendering of info windows.

avoidFerries.!doc: If true, instructs the Directions service to avoid ferries where possible. Optional.

avoidHighways.!doc: If true, instructs the Directions service to avoid highways where possible. Optional.

avoidTolls.!doc: If true, instructs the Directions service to avoid toll roads where possible. Optional.

destination.!doc: Location of destination. This can be specified as either a string to be geocoded or a LatLng. Required.

durationInTraffic.!doc: Whether or not we should provide trip duration based on current traffic conditions. Only available to Maps API for Work customers.

optimizeWaypoints.!doc: If set to true, the DirectionService will attempt to re-order the supplied intermediate waypoints to minimize overall cost of the route. If waypoints are optimized, inspect DirectionsRoute.waypoint_order in the response to determine the new ordering.

origin.!doc: Location of origin. This can be specified as either a string to be geocoded or a LatLng. Required.

provideRouteAlternatives.!doc: Whether or not route alternatives should be provided. Optional.

region.!doc: Region code used as a bias for geocoding requests. Optional.

transitOptions.!doc: Settings that apply only to requests where travelMode is TRANSIT. This object will have no effect for other travel modes.

unitSystem.!doc: Preferred unit system to use when displaying distance. Defaults to the unit system used in the country of origin.

waypoints.!doc: Array of intermediate waypoints. Directions will be calculated from the origin to the destination by way of each waypoint in this array. The maximum allowed waypoints is 8, plus the origin, and destination. Maps API for Business customers are allowed 23 waypoints, plus the origin, and destination. Waypoints are not supported for transit directions. Optional.

routes.!doc: An array of DirectionsRoutes, each of which contains information about the legs and steps of which it is composed. There will only be one route unless the DirectionsRequest was made with provideRouteAlternatives set to true.

copyrights.!doc: Copyrights text to be displayed for this route.

fare.!doc: The total fare for the whole transit trip. Only applicable to transit requests.

legs.!doc: An array of DirectionsLegs, each of which contains information about the steps of which it is composed. There will be one leg for each waypoint or destination specified. So a route with no waypoints will contain one DirectionsLeg and a route with one waypoint will contain two.

overview_path.!doc: An array of LatLngs representing the entire course of this route. The path is simplified in order to make it suitable in contexts where a small number of vertices is required (such as Static Maps API URLs).

overview_polyline.!doc: An encoded polyline representation of the route in overview_path. This polyline is an approximate (smoothed) path of the resulting directions.

warnings.!doc: Warnings to be displayed when showing these directions.

waypoint_order.!doc: If optimizeWaypoints was set to true, this field will contain the re-ordered permutation of the input waypoints. For example, if the input was:   Origin: Los Angeles   Waypoints: Dallas, Bangor, Phoenix   Destination: New York and the optimized output was ordered as follows:   Origin: Los Angeles   Waypoints: Phoenix, Dallas, Bangor   Destination: New York then this field will be an Array containing the values [2, 0, 1]. Note that the numbering of waypoints is zero-based. If any of the input waypoints has stopover set to false, this field will be empty, since route optimization is not available for such queries.

distance.!doc: The distance covered by this step. This property may be undefined as the distance may be unknown.

duration.!doc: The typical time required to perform this step in seconds and in text form. This property may be undefined as the duration may be unknown.

end_location.!doc: The ending location of this step.

path.!doc: A sequence of LatLngs describing the course of this step.

start_location.!doc: The starting location of this step.

steps.!doc: Sub-steps of this step. Specified for non-transit sections of transit routes.

transit.!doc: Transit-specific details about this step. This property will be undefined unless the travel mode of this step is TRANSIT.

travel_mode.!doc: The mode of travel used in this step.

location.!doc: Waypoint location. Can be an address string or LatLng. Optional.

stopover.!doc: If true, indicates that this waypoint is a stop between the origin and destination. This has the effect of splitting the route into two. This value is true by default. Optional.

text.!doc: A string representation of the distance value, using the UnitSystem specified in the request.

avoidFerries.!doc: If true, instructs the Distance Matrix service to avoid ferries where possible. Optional.

avoidHighways.!doc: If true, instructs the Distance Matrix service to avoid highways where possible. Optional.

avoidTolls.!doc: If true, instructs the Distance Matrix service to avoid toll roads where possible. Optional.

destinations.!doc: An array containing destination address strings and/or LatLngs, to which to calculate distance and time. Required.

durationInTraffic.!doc: Whether or not we should provide trip durations based on current traffic conditions. Only available to Maps API for Work customers.

origins.!doc: An array containing origin address strings and/or LatLngs, from which to calculate distance and time. Required.

region.!doc: Region code used as a bias for geocoding requests. Optional.

transitOptions.!doc: Settings that apply only to requests where travelMode is TRANSIT. This object will have no effect for other travel modes.

unitSystem.!doc: Preferred unit system to use when displaying distance. Optional; defaults to metric.

rows.!doc: The rows of the matrix, corresponding to the origin addresses.

distance.!doc: The distance for this origin-destination pairing. This property may be undefined as the distance may be unknown.

duration.!doc: The duration for this origin-destination pairing. This property may be undefined as the duration may be unknown.

fare.!doc: The total fare for this origin-destination pairing. Only applicable to transit requests.

status.!doc: The status of this particular origin-destination pairing.

elements.!doc: The row's elements, corresponding to the destination addresses.

drawingModes.!doc: The drawing modes to display in the drawing control, in the order in which they are to be displayed. The hand icon (which corresponds to the null drawing mode) is always available and is not to be specified in this array. Defaults to [MARKER, POLYLINE, RECTANGLE, CIRCLE, POLYGON].

position.!doc: Position id. Used to specify the position of the control on the map. The default position is TOP_LEFT.

circleOptions.!doc: Options to apply to any new circles created with this DrawingManager. The center and radius properties are ignored, and the map property of a new circle is always set to the DrawingManager's map.

drawingControl.!doc: The enabled/disabled state of the drawing control. Defaults to true.

drawingControlOptions.!doc: The display options for the drawing control.

drawingMode.!doc: The DrawingManager's drawing mode, which defines the type of overlay to be added on the map. Accepted values are MARKER, POLYGON, POLYLINE, RECTANGLE, CIRCLE, or null. A drawing mode of null means that the user can interact with the map as normal, and clicks do not draw anything.

map.!doc: The Map to which the DrawingManager is attached, which is the Map on which the overlays created will be placed.

markerOptions.!doc: Options to apply to any new markers created with this DrawingManager. The position property is ignored, and the map property of a new marker is always set to the DrawingManager's map.

polygonOptions.!doc: Options to apply to any new polygons created with this DrawingManager. The paths property is ignored, and the map property of a new polygon is always set to the DrawingManager's map.

polylineOptions.!doc: Options to apply to any new polylines created with this DrawingManager. The path property is ignored, and the map property of a new polyline is always set to the DrawingManager's map.

rectangleOptions.!doc: Options to apply to any new rectangles created with this DrawingManager. The bounds property is ignored, and the map property of a new rectangle is always set to the DrawingManager's map.

text.!doc: A string representation of the duration value.

accessToken.!doc: The authentication token returned by an OAuth 2.0 authentication request.

clickable.!doc: If true, the layer receives mouse events. Default value is true.

layerId.!doc: The ID of the Maps Engine layer to display.

layerKey.!doc: The key of the layer to display from the specified map.

map.!doc: The map on which to display the layer.

mapId.!doc: The ID of the Maps Engine map that contains the layer with the given layerKey.

opacity.!doc: The opacity of the layer, expressed as a number between 0 and 1. Defaults to 1. Applies only to imagery layers. Note: Be careful of setting this option for other layer types, as it may become effective in the future.

suppressInfoWindows.!doc: Suppress the rendering of info windows when layer features are clicked.

featureId.!doc: The feature ID, guaranteed to be unique within the layer.

getDetails.!doc: Takes a callback that will be called with details about the feature that may be used to render an info window.

latLng.!doc: The latitude/longitude that was below the cursor when the event occurred.

elevation.!doc: The elevation of this point on Earth, in meters above sea level.

location.!doc: The location of this elevation result.

resolution.!doc: The distance, in meters, between sample points from which the elevation was interpolated. This property will be missing if the resolution is not known. Note that elevation data becomes more coarse (larger resolution values) when multiple points are passed. To obtain the most accurate elevation value for a point, it should be queried independently.

fillColor.!doc: The feature's fill color. All CSS3 colors are supported except for extended named colors.

fillOpacity.!doc: Fill opacity, expressed as a decimal between 0 and 1 inclusive. This property may be set as a number, but it will always be returned as a string.

iconAnchor.!doc: The icon's anchor point is the pixel in the source image that is aligned with the point's geographical location, expressed as a whitespace-separated pair of numbers: x y. Defaults to the center of the icon.

iconClip.!doc: The rectangular region of the icon's image (in image pixel coordinates) to use, as a whitespace-separated 4-tuple of numbers: x y width height. For example, to use a 32x32 icon situated at (0, 64) in a sprite sheet, specify 0 64 32 32.

iconImage.!doc: The image to render at the point. Currently, only url(...) is supported.

iconOpacity.!doc: Icon opacity, expressed as a decimal between 0 and 1 inclusive. This property may be set as a number, but it will always be returned as a string.

iconSize.!doc: Icon size, expressed as a string with two measurements (with pixel or percentage as unit) separated by whitespace.

reset.!doc: Resets the given style property to its original value.

resetAll.!doc: Resets all style properties to their original values.

strokeColor.!doc: The feature's stroke color. All CSS3 colors are supported except for extended named colors.

strokeOpacity.!doc: Stroke opacity, expressed as a decimal between 0 and 1 inclusive. This property may be set as a number, but it will always be returned as a string.

strokeWidth.!doc: Stroke width in pixels. This property may be set as a number, but it will always be returned as a string.

zIndex.!doc: Rendering order. Features with greater zIndex are rendered on top.

columnName.!doc: The name of the column in which the cell was located.

enabled.!doc: If true, render the layer as a heatmap.

clickable.!doc: If true, the layer receives mouse events. Default value is true.

heatmap.!doc: Options which define the appearance of the layer as a heatmap.

map.!doc: The map on which to display the layer.

query.!doc: Options defining the data to display.

styles.!doc: An array of up to 5 style specifications, which control the appearance of features within the layer.

suppressInfoWindows.!doc: Suppress the rendering of info windows when layer features are clicked.

iconName.!doc: The name of a Fusion Tables  supported icon

infoWindowHtml.!doc: Pre-rendered HTML content, as placed in the infowindow by the default UI.

latLng.!doc: The position at which to anchor an infowindow on the clicked feature.

pixelOffset.!doc: The offset to apply to an infowindow anchored on the clicked feature.

row.!doc: A collection of FusionTablesCell objects, indexed by column name, representing the contents of the table row which included the clicked feature.

fillColor.!doc: The fill color, defined by a six-digit hexadecimal number in RRGGBB format (e.g. #00AAFF).

strokeColor.!doc: The fill color, defined by a six-digit hexadecimal number in RRGGBB format (e.g. #00AAFF).

strokeWeight.!doc: The stroke width in pixels, between 0 and 10.

strokeColor.!doc: The fill color, defined by a six-digit hexadecimal number in RRGGBB format (e.g. #00AAFF).

from.!doc: The ID of the Fusion Tables table to display. This ID can be found in the table's URL, as the value of the dsrcid parameter. Required.

limit.!doc: Limit on the number of results returned by the query.

orderBy.!doc: The method by which to sort the results. Accepts either of:  A column name. The column name may be suffixed with ASC or DESC (e.g. col2 DESC) to specify ascending or descending sort.   An ST_DISTANCE spatial relationship (sort by distance). A column and the coordinate from which to calculate distance must be passed, for example, orderBy: 'ST_DISTANCE(col1, LATLNG(1.2, 3.4))'.

select.!doc: A column, containing geographic features to be displayed on the map. See  Fusion Tables Setup in the Maps API documentation for information about valid columns.

where.!doc: The SQL predicate to be applied to the layer.

markerOptions.!doc: Options which control the appearance of point features.

polygonOptions.!doc: Options which control the appearance of polygons.

polylineOptions.!doc: Options which control the appearance of polylines.

where.!doc: The SQL predicate to be applied to the layer.

long_name.!doc: The full text of the address component

short_name.!doc: The abbreviated, short text of the given address component

types.!doc: An array of strings denoting the type of this address component. A list of valid types can be found here

administrativeArea.!doc: Matches all the administrative_area levels. Optional.

country.!doc: Matches a country name or a two letter ISO 3166-1 country code. Optional.

locality.!doc: Matches against both locality and sublocality types. Optional.

route.!doc: Matches the long or short name of a route. Optional.

bounds.!doc: The precise bounds of this GeocoderResult, if applicable

location.!doc: The latitude/longitude coordinates of this result

location_type.!doc: The type of location returned in location

viewport.!doc: The bounds of the recommended viewport for displaying this GeocoderResult

bounds.!doc: LatLngBounds within which to search. Optional.

componentRestrictions.!doc: Components are used to restrict results to a specific area. A filter consists of one or more of: route, locality, administrativeArea, postalCode, country. Only the results that match all the filters will be returned. Filter values support the same methods of spelling correction and partial matching as other geocoding requests. Optional.

location.!doc: LatLng about which to search. Optional.

region.!doc: Country code used to bias the search, specified as a Unicode region subtag / CLDR identifier. Optional.

formatted_address.!doc: A string containing the human-readable address of this location.

partial_match.!doc: Whether the geocoder did not return an exact match for the original request, though it was able to match part of the requested address.

postcode_localities.!doc: An array of strings denoting all the localities contained in a postal code. This is only present when the result is a postal code that contains multiple localities.

types.!doc: An array of strings denoting the type of the returned geocoded element. For a list of possible strings, refer to the  Address Component Types section of the Developer's Guide.

clickable.!doc: If true, the ground overlay can receive mouse events.

map.!doc: The map on which to display the overlay.

opacity.!doc: The opacity of the overlay, expressed as a number between 0 and 1. Optional. Defaults to 1.

data.!doc: The data points to display. Required.

dissipating.!doc: Specifies whether heatmaps dissipate on zoom. By default, the radius of influence of a data point is specified by the radius option only. When dissipating is disabled, the radius option is intepreted as a radius at zoom level 0.

gradient.!doc: The color gradient of the heatmap, specified as an array of CSS color strings. All CSS3 colors are supported except for extended named colors.

map.!doc: The map on which to display the layer.

maxIntensity.!doc: The maximum intensity of the heatmap. By default, heatmap colors are dynamically scaled according to the greatest concentration of points at any particular pixel on the map. This property allows you to specify a fixed maximum.

opacity.!doc: The opacity of the heatmap, expressed as a number between 0 and 1. Defaults to 0.6.

radius.!doc: The radius of influence for each data point, in pixels.

anchor.!doc: The position at which to anchor an image in correspondence to the location of the marker on the map. By default, the anchor is located along the center point of the bottom of the image.

origin.!doc: The position of the image within a sprite, if any. By default, the origin is located at the top left corner of the image (0, 0).

scaledSize.!doc: The size of the entire image after scaling, if any. Use this property to stretch/shrink an image or a sprite.

size.!doc: The display size of the sprite or image. When using sprites, you must specify the sprite size. If the size is not provided, it will be set when the image loads.

url.!doc: The URL of the image or sprite sheet.

fixedRotation.!doc: If true, each icon in the sequence has the same fixed rotation regardless of the angle of the edge on which it lies. Defaults to false, in which case each icon in the sequence is rotated to align with its edge.

icon.!doc: The icon to render on the line.

offset.!doc: The distance from the start of the line at which an icon is to be rendered. This distance may be expressed as a percentage of line's length (e.g. '50%') or in pixels (e.g. '50px'). Defaults to '100%'.

repeat.!doc: The distance between consecutive icons on the line. This distance may be expressed as a percentage of the line's length (e.g. '50%') or in pixels (e.g. '50px'). To disable repeating of the icon, specify '0'. Defaults to '0'.

alt.!doc: Alt text to display when this MapType's button is hovered over in the MapTypeControl.

getTileUrl.!doc: Returns a string (URL) for given tile coordinate (x, y) and zoom level.

maxZoom.!doc: The maximum zoom level for the map when displaying this MapType.

minZoom.!doc: The minimum zoom level for the map when displaying this MapType. Optional.

name.!doc: Name to display in the MapTypeControl.

opacity.!doc: The opacity to apply to the tiles. The opacity should be specified as a float value between 0 and 1.0, where 0 is fully transparent and 1 is fully opaque.

content.!doc: Content to display in the InfoWindow. This can be an HTML element, a plain-text string, or a string containing HTML. The InfoWindow will be sized according to the content. To set an explicit size for the content, set content to be a HTML element with that size.

disableAutoPan.!doc: Disable auto-pan on open. By default, the info window will pan the map so that it is fully visible when it opens.

maxWidth.!doc: Maximum width of the infowindow, regardless of content's width. This value is only considered if it is set before a call to open. To change the maximum width when changing content, call close, setOptions, and then open.

pixelOffset.!doc: The offset, in pixels, of the tip of the info window from the point on the map at whose geographical coordinates the info window is anchored. If an InfoWindow is opened with an anchor, the pixelOffset will be calculated from the anchor's anchorPoint property.

position.!doc: The LatLng at which to display this InfoWindow. If the InfoWindow is opened with an anchor, the anchor's position will be used instead.

zIndex.!doc: All InfoWindows are displayed on the map in order of their zIndex, with higher values displaying in front of InfoWindows with lower values. By default, InfoWindows are displayed according to their latitude, with InfoWindows of lower latitudes appearing in front of InfoWindows at higher latitudes. InfoWindows are always displayed in front of markers.

email.!doc: The author's e-mail address, or an empty string if not specified.

name.!doc: The author's name, or an empty string if not specified.

uri.!doc: The author's home page, or an empty string if not specified.

author.!doc: The feature's <atom:author>, extracted from the layer markup (if specified).

description.!doc: The feature's <description>, extracted from the layer markup.

id.!doc: The feature's <id>, extracted from the layer markup. If no <id> has been specified, a unique ID will be generated for this feature.

infoWindowHtml.!doc: The feature's balloon styled text, if set.

name.!doc: The feature's <name>, extracted from the layer markup.

snippet.!doc: The feature's <Snippet>, extracted from the layer markup.

author.!doc: The layer's <atom:author>, extracted from the layer markup.

description.!doc: The layer's <description>, extracted from the layer markup.

hasScreenOverlays.!doc: Whether the layer has any screen overlays.

name.!doc: The layer's <name>, extracted from the layer markup.

snippet.!doc: The layer's <Snippet>, extracted from the layer markup

clickable.!doc: If true, the layer receives mouse events. Default value is true.

map.!doc: The map on which to display the layer.

preserveViewport.!doc: By default, the input map is centered and zoomed to the bounding box of the contents of the layer. If this option is set to true, the viewport is left unchanged, unless the map's center and zoom were never set.

screenOverlays.!doc: Whether to render the screen overlays. Default true.

suppressInfoWindows.!doc: Suppress the rendering of info windows when layer features are clicked.

url.!doc: The URL of the KML document to display.

featureData.!doc: A KmlFeatureData object, containing information about the clicked feature.

latLng.!doc: The position at which to anchor an infowindow on the clicked feature.

pixelOffset.!doc: The offset to apply to an infowindow anchored on the clicked feature.

lat.!doc: Latitude in degrees. Values will be clamped to the range [-90, 90]. This means that if the value specified is less than -90, it will be set to -90. And if the value is greater than 90, it will be set to 90.

lng.!doc: Longitude in degrees. Values outside the range [-180, 180] will be wrapped so that they fall within the range. For example, a value of -190 will be converted to 170. A value of 190 will be converted to -170. This reflects the fact that longitudes wrap around the globe.

locations.!doc: The discrete locations for which to retrieve elevations.

fromContainerPixelToLatLng.!doc: Computes the geographical coordinates from pixel coordinates in the map's container.

fromDivPixelToLatLng.!doc: Computes the geographical coordinates from pixel coordinates in the div that holds the draggable map.

fromLatLngToContainerPixel.!doc: Computes the pixel coordinates of the given geographical location in the map's container element.

fromLatLngToDivPixel.!doc: Computes the pixel coordinates of the given geographical location in the DOM element that holds the draggable map.

getWorldWidth.!doc: The width of the world in pixels in the current zoom level. For projections with a heading angle of either 90 or 270 degrees, this corresponds to the pixel span in the Y-axis.

backgroundColor.!doc: Color used for the background of the Map div. This color will be visible when tiles have not yet loaded as the user pans. This option can only be set when the map is initialized.

disableDefaultUI.!doc: Enables/disables all default UI. May be overridden individually.

disableDoubleClickZoom.!doc: Enables/disables zoom and center on double click. Enabled by default.

draggable.!doc: If false, prevents the map from being dragged. Dragging is enabled by default.

draggableCursor.!doc: The name or url of the cursor to display when mousing over a draggable map. This property uses the css cursor attribute to change the icon. As with the css property, you must specify at least one fallback cursor that is not a URL. For example: draggableCursor: 'url(http://www.example.com/icon.png), auto;'.

draggingCursor.!doc: The name or url of the cursor to display when the map is being dragged. This property uses the css cursor attribute to change the icon. As with the css property, you must specify at least one fallback cursor that is not a URL. For example: draggingCursor: 'url(http://www.example.com/icon.png), auto;'.

heading.!doc: The heading for aerial imagery in degrees measured clockwise from cardinal direction North. Headings are snapped to the nearest available angle for which imagery is available.

keyboardShortcuts.!doc: If false, prevents the map from being controlled by the keyboard. Keyboard shortcuts are enabled by default.

mapMaker.!doc: True if Map Maker tiles should be used instead of regular tiles.

mapTypeControl.!doc: The initial enabled/disabled state of the Map type control.

mapTypeControlOptions.!doc: The initial display options for the Map type control.

mapTypeId.!doc: The initial Map mapTypeId. Defaults to ROADMAP.

maxZoom.!doc: The maximum zoom level which will be displayed on the map. If omitted, or set to null, the maximum zoom from the current map type is used instead.

minZoom.!doc: The minimum zoom level which will be displayed on the map. If omitted, or set to null, the minimum zoom from the current map type is used instead.

noClear.!doc: If true, do not clear the contents of the Map div.

overviewMapControl.!doc: The enabled/disabled state of the Overview Map control.

overviewMapControlOptions.!doc: The display options for the Overview Map control.

panControl.!doc: The enabled/disabled state of the Pan control.

panControlOptions.!doc: The display options for the Pan control.

rotateControl.!doc: The enabled/disabled state of the Rotate control.

rotateControlOptions.!doc: The display options for the Rotate control.

scaleControl.!doc: The initial enabled/disabled state of the Scale control.

scaleControlOptions.!doc: The initial display options for the Scale control.

scrollwheel.!doc: If false, disables scrollwheel zooming on the map. The scrollwheel is enabled by default.

streetView.!doc: A StreetViewPanorama to display when the Street View pegman is dropped on the map. If no panorama is specified, a default StreetViewPanorama will be displayed in the map's div when the pegman is dropped.

streetViewControl.!doc: The initial enabled/disabled state of the Street View Pegman control. This control is part of the default UI, and should be set to false when displaying a map type on which the Street View road overlay should not appear (e.g. a non-Earth map type).

streetViewControlOptions.!doc: The initial display options for the Street View Pegman control.

styles.!doc: Styles to apply to each of the default map types. Note that for Satellite/Hybrid and Terrain modes, these styles will only apply to labels and geometry.

tilt.!doc: Controls the automatic switching behavior for the angle of incidence of the map. The only allowed values are 0 and 45. The value 0 causes the map to always use a 0° overhead view regardless of the zoom level and viewport. The value 45 causes the tilt angle to automatically switch to 45 whenever 45° imagery is available for the current zoom level and viewport, and switch back to 0 whenever 45° imagery is not available (this is the default behavior). 45° imagery is only available for SATELLITE and HYBRID map types, within some locations, and at some zoom levels. Note: getTilt returns the current tilt angle, not the value specified by this option. Because getTilt and this option refer to different things, do not bind() the tilt property; doing so may yield unpredictable effects.

zoom.!doc: The initial Map zoom level. Required.

zoomControl.!doc: The enabled/disabled state of the Zoom control.

zoomControlOptions.!doc: The display options for the Zoom control.

floatPane.!doc: This pane contains the info window. It is above all map overlays. (Pane 4).

mapPane.!doc: This pane is the lowest pane and is above the tiles. It may not receive DOM events. (Pane 0).

markerLayer.!doc: This pane contains markers. It may not receive DOM events. (Pane 2).

overlayLayer.!doc: This pane contains polylines, polygons, ground overlays and tile layer overlays. It may not receive DOM events. (Pane 1).

overlayMouseTarget.!doc: This pane contains elements that receive DOM events. (Pane 3).

alt.!doc: Alt text to display when this MapType's button is hovered over in the MapTypeControl. Optional.

getTile.!doc: Returns a tile for the given tile coordinate (x, y) and zoom level. This tile will be appended to the given ownerDocument. Not available for base map types.
getTile.!type: fn(tileCoord: google.maps.Point, zoom: number, ownerDocument: Document) -> Node

maxZoom.!doc: The maximum zoom level for the map when displaying this MapType. Required for base MapTypes, ignored for overlay MapTypes.

minZoom.!doc: The minimum zoom level for the map when displaying this MapType. Optional; defaults to 0.

name.!doc: Name to display in the MapTypeControl. Optional.

projection.!doc: The Projection used to render this MapType. Optional; defaults to Mercator.

radius.!doc: Radius of the planet for the map, in meters. Optional; defaults to Earth's equatorial radius of 6378137 meters.

releaseTile.!doc: Releases the given tile, performing any necessary cleanup. The provided tile will have already been removed from the document. Optional.

tileSize.!doc: The dimensions of each tile. Required.

mapTypeIds.!doc: IDs of map types to show in the control.

position.!doc: Position id. Used to specify the position of the control on the map. The default position is TOP_RIGHT.

style.!doc: Style id. Used to select what style of map type control to display.

elementType.!doc: Selects the element type to which a styler should be applied. An element type distinguishes between the different representations of a feature. Optional; if elementType is not specified, the value is assumed to be 'all'.

featureType.!doc: Selects the feature, or group of features, to which a styler should be applied. Optional; if featureType is not specified, the value is assumed to be 'all'.

stylers.!doc: The style rules to apply to the selectors. The rules are applied to the map's elements in the order they are listed in this array.

all.!doc: Apply the rule to all elements of the specified feature.

geometry.!doc: Apply the rule to the feature's geometry.

geometry.fill.!doc: Apply the rule to the fill of the feature's geometry.

geometry.stroke.!doc: Apply the rule to the stroke of the feature's geometry.

labels.!doc: Apply the rule to the feature's labels.

labels.icon.!doc: Apply the rule to icons within the feature's labels.

labels.text.!doc: Apply the rule to the text in the feature's label.

labels.text.fill.!doc: Apply the rule to the fill of the text in the feature's labels.

labels.text.stroke.!doc: Apply the rule to the stroke of the text in the feature's labels.

administrative.!doc: Apply the rule to administrative areas.

administrative.land_parcel.!doc: Apply the rule to land parcels.

all.!doc: Apply the rule to all selector types.

landscape.man_made.!doc: Apply the rule to man made structures.

landscape.natural.!doc: Apply the rule to natural features.

poi.!doc: Apply the rule to points of interest.

poi.attraction.!doc: Apply the rule to attractions for tourists.

poi.government.!doc: Apply the rule to government buildings.

poi.medical.!doc: Apply the rule to emergency services (hospitals, pharmacies, police, doctors, etc).

poi.place_of_worship.!doc: Apply the rule to places of worship, such as churches, temples, or mosques.

poi.sports_complex.!doc: Apply the rule to sports complexes.

road.!doc: Apply the rule to all roads.

road.arterial.!doc: Apply the rule to arterial roads.

road.highway.controlled_access.!doc: Apply the rule to controlled-access highways.

road.local.!doc: Apply the rule to local roads.

transit.!doc: Apply the rule to all transit stations and lines.

transit.line.!doc: Apply the rule to transit lines.

transit.station.!doc: Apply the rule to all transit stations.

transit.station.bus.!doc: Apply the rule to bus stops.

transit.station.rail.!doc: Apply the rule to rail stations.

water.!doc: Apply the rule to bodies of water.

color.!doc: Sets the color of the feature. Valid values: An RGB hex string, i.e. '#ff0000'.

gamma.!doc: Modifies the gamma by raising the lightness to the given power. Valid values: Floating point numbers, [0.01, 10], with 1.0 representing no change.

hue.!doc: Sets the hue of the feature to match the hue of the color supplied. Note that the saturation and lightness of the feature is conserved, which means that the feature will not match the color supplied exactly. Valid values: An RGB hex string, i.e. '#ff0000'.

invert_lightness.!doc: A value of true will invert the lightness of the feature while preserving the hue and saturation.

lightness.!doc: Shifts lightness of colors by a percentage of the original value if decreasing and a percentage of the remaining value if increasing. Valid values: [-100, 100].

saturation.!doc: Shifts the saturation of colors by a percentage of the original value if decreasing and a percentage of the remaining value if increasing. Valid values: [-100, 100].

visibility.!doc: Sets the visibility of the feature. Valid values: 'on', 'off' or 'simplifed'.

weight.!doc: Sets the weight of the feature, in pixels. Valid values: Integers greater than or equal to zero.

accessToken.!doc: The authentication token returned by an OAuth 2.0 authentication request.

clickable.!doc: If true, the layer receives mouse events. Default value is true.

fitBounds.!doc: If this option is set to true, the map viewport is centered and zoomed to the bounding box of the contents of the layer. Default value is false. Applies only to KML layers. Note: Be careful when setting this option for other layer types, as it may become effective in the future.

layerId.!doc: The ID of a single Maps Engine layer to display.

layerKey.!doc: The key of the layer to display. Maps Engine layer keys are only unique within a single map, and can be changed by map owners.

map.!doc: The map on which to display the layer.

mapId.!doc: The ID of the Maps Engine map that contains the layer with the given layerKey.

opacity.!doc: The opacity of the layer, expressed as a number between 0 and 1. Defaults to 1. Applies only to imagery layers. Note: Be careful of setting this option for other layer types, as it may become effective in the future.

suppressInfoWindows.!doc: Suppress the rendering of info windows when layer features are clicked.

zIndex.!doc: The z-index of the layer. Only applies to Vector and KML layers.

featureId.!doc: The feature ID, guaranteed to be unique within the layer.

infoWindowHtml.!doc: Pre-rendered HTML content, as placed in the infowindow by the default UI.

latLng.!doc: The position at which to anchor an infowindow on the clicked feature.

pixelOffset.!doc: The offset to apply to an infowindow anchored on the clicked feature.

INVALID_LAYER.!doc: The requested layer is not a valid layer.

UNKNOWN_ERROR.!doc: The layer failed to load for an unknown reason.

anchorPoint.!doc: The offset from the marker's position to the tip of an InfoWindow that has been opened with the marker as anchor.

animation.!doc: Which animation to play when marker is added to a map.

attribution.!doc: Contains all the information needed to identify your application as the source of a save. In this context, 'place' means a business, point of interest or geographic location. attribution must be specified with a place in order to enable a save.

clickable.!doc: If true, the marker receives mouse and touch events. Default value is true.

crossOnDrag.!doc: If false, disables cross that appears beneath the marker when dragging. This option is true by default.

cursor.!doc: Mouse cursor to show on hover

draggable.!doc: If true, the marker can be dragged. Default value is false.

icon.!doc: Icon for the foreground. If a string is provided, it is treated as though it were an Icon with the string as url.

map.!doc: Map on which to display Marker.

optimized.!doc: Optimization renders many markers as a single static element. Optimized rendering is enabled by default. Disable optimized rendering for animated GIFs or PNGs, or when each marker must be rendered as a separate DOM element (advanced usage only).

place.!doc: Place information, used to identify and describe the place associated with this Marker. In this context, 'place' means a business, point of interest or geographic location. To allow a user to save this place, open an info window anchored on this marker. The info window will contain information about the place and an option for the user to save it. Only one of position or place can be specified.

shape.!doc: Image map region definition used for drag/click.

visible.!doc: If true, the marker is visible

zIndex.!doc: All markers are displayed on the map in order of their zIndex, with higher values displaying in front of markers with lower values. By default, markers are displayed according to their vertical position on screen, with lower markers appearing in front of markers further up the screen.

coords.!doc: The format of this attribute depends on the value of the type and follows the w3 AREA coords specification found at  http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/struct/objects.html#adef-coords. The coords attribute is an array of integers that specify the pixel position of the shape relative to the top-left corner of the target image. The coordinates depend on the value of type as follows:   - circle: coords is [x1,y1,r] where x1,y2 are the coordinates of the center of the circle, and r is the radius of the circle.   - poly: coords is [x1,y1,x2,y2...xn,yn] where each x,y pair contains the coordinates of one vertex of the polygon.   - rect: coords is [x1,y1,x2,y2] where x1,y1 are the coordinates of the upper-left corner of the rectangle and x2,y2 are the coordinates of the lower-right coordinates of the rectangle.

type.!doc: Describes the shape's type and can be circle, poly or rect.

zoom.!doc: The maximum zoom level found at the given LatLng.

latLng.!doc: The latitude/longitude that was below the cursor when the event occurred.

stop.!doc: Prevents this event from propagating further.

opened.!doc: Whether the control should display in opened mode or collapsed (minimized) mode. By default, the control is closed.

position.!doc: Position id. Used to specify the position of the control on the map. The default position is TOP_LEFT.

author.!doc: The username of the user who uploaded this photo.

photoId.!doc: The unique identifier for this photo, as used in the Panoramio API (see http://www.panoramio.com/api/widget/api.html).

userId.!doc: The unique identifier for the user who uploaded this photo, as used in the Panoramio API (see http://www.panoramio.com/api/widget/api.html).

clickable.!doc: If true, the layer receives mouse events. Default value is true.

map.!doc: The map on which to display the layer.

suppressInfoWindows.!doc: Suppress the rendering of info windows when layer features are clicked.

tag.!doc: A panoramio tag used to filter the photos which are displayed. Only photos which have been tagged with the supplied string will be shown.

userId.!doc: A Panoramio user ID. If provided, only photos by this user will be displayed on the map. If both a tag and user ID are provided, the tag will take precedence.

featureDetails.!doc: A PanoramioFeature object containing information about the clicked feature.

infoWindowHtml.!doc: Pre-rendered HTML content to display within a feature's InfoWindow when clicked.

latLng.!doc: The position at which to anchor an info window on the clicked feature.

pixelOffset.!doc: The offset to apply to an info window anchored on the clicked feature.

path.!doc: The path along which to collect elevation values.

samples.!doc: Required. The number of equidistant points along the given path for which to retrieve elevation data, including the endpoints. The number of samples must be a value between 2 and 512 inclusive.

maxHeight.!doc: The maximum height in pixels of the returned image.

maxWidth.!doc: The maximum width in pixels of the returned image.

location.!doc: The LatLng of the entity described by this Place. This must be provided for the Place to be considered valid.

placeId.!doc: The place ID of the place (such as a business or point of interest). The place ID is a unique identifier of a place in the Google Maps database. Note that the placeId is the most accurate way of identifying a place. If possible, you should specify the placeId rather than a placeQuery. A place ID can be retrieved from any request to the Places API, such as a  TextSearch.

query.!doc: A search query describing the place (such as a business or point of interest). An example query would be "Quay, Upper Level, Overseas Passenger Terminal 5 Hickson Road, The Rocks NSW". If possible, you should specify the placeId rather than a placeQuery. The API does not guarantee the accuracy of resolving the query string to a place. If both the placeId and placeQuery are provided, an error is thrown.

rating.!doc: The rating of this aspect. For individual reviews this is an integer from 0 to 3. For aggregated ratings of a place this is an integer from 0 to 30.

placeId.!doc: The Place ID of the Place for which details are being requested.

viewport.!doc: The preferred viewport when displaying this Place on a map. This property will be null if the preferred viewport for the Place is not known.

getUrl.!doc: Returns the image URL corresponding to the specified options. You must include a PhotoOptions object with at least one of maxWidth or maxHeight specified.

height.!doc: The height of the photo in pixels.

html_attributions.!doc: Attribution text to be displayed for this photo.

width.!doc: The width of the photo in pixels.

address_components.!doc: The collection of address components for this Place's location.

aspects.!doc: The rated aspects of this Place, based on Google and Zagat user reviews. The ratings are on a scale of 0 to 30.

formatted_phone_number.!doc: The Place's phone number, formatted according to the  number's regional convention.

html_attributions.!doc: Attribution text to be displayed for this Place result.

icon.!doc: URL to an image resource that can be used to represent this Place's category.

international_phone_number.!doc: The Place's phone number in international format. International format includes the country code, and is prefixed with the plus (+) sign.

name.!doc: The Place's name. Note: In the case of user entered Places, this is the raw text, as typed by the user. Please exercise caution when using this data, as malicious users may try to use it as a vector for code injection attacks (See  http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Code_injection).

permanently_closed.!doc: A flag indicating whether the Place is permanently closed. If the place is not permanently closed, the flag is not present in search or details responses.

photos.!doc: Photos of this Place. The collection will contain up to ten PlacePhoto objects.

place_id.!doc: A unique identifier for a place.

price_level.!doc: The price level of the Place, on a scale of 0 to 4. Price levels are interpreted as follows: Value Description 0 Free 1 Inexpensive 2 Moderate 3 Expensive 4 Very Expensive

rating.!doc: A rating, between 1.0 to 5.0, based on user reviews of this Place.

reviews.!doc: A list of reviews of this Place.

types.!doc: An array of types for this Place (e.g., ["political",  "locality"] or ["restaurant", "establishment"]).

url.!doc: URL of the official Google page for this place. This will be the establishment's Google+ page if the Google+ page exists, otherwise it will be the Google-owned page that contains the best available information about the place.

vicinity.!doc: A fragment of the Place's address for disambiguation (usually street name and locality).

website.!doc: The authoritative website for this Place, such as a business' homepage.

aspects.!doc: The aspects rated by the review. The ratings on a scale of 0 to 3.

author_url.!doc: A link to the reviewer's profile. This will be undefined when the reviewer's profile is unavailable.

language.!doc: An IETF language code indicating the language in which this review is written. Note that this code includes only the main language tag without any secondary tag indicating country or region. For example, all the English reviews are tagged as 'en' rather than 'en-AU' or 'en-UK'.

hasNextPage.!doc: Indicates if further results are available. true when there is an additional results page.

nextPage.!doc: Fetches the next page of results. Uses the same callback function that was provided to the first search request.

bounds.!doc: The bounds within which to search for Places. Both location and radius will be ignored if bounds is set.

keyword.!doc: A term to be matched against all available fields, including but not limited to name, type, and address, as well as customer reviews and other third-party content.

location.!doc: The location around which to search for Places.

maxPriceLevel.!doc: Restricts results to only those places at the specified price level or lower. Valid values are in the range from 0 (most affordable) to 4 (most expensive), inclusive. Must be greater than or equal to minPrice , if specified.

minPriceLevel.!doc: Restricts results to only those places at the specified price level or higher. Valid values are in the range from 0 (most affordable) to 4 (most expensive), inclusive. Must be less than or equal to maxPrice, if specified.

name.!doc: Restricts the Place search results to Places that include this text in the name.

openNow.!doc: Restricts results to only those places that are open right now.

radius.!doc: The distance from the given location within which to search for Places, in meters. The maximum allowed value is 50 000.

rankBy.!doc: Specifies the ranking method to use when returning results.

types.!doc: Restricts the Place search results to Places with a type matching at least one of the specified types in this array. Valid types are given here.

edge.!doc: The index of the edge within the path beneath the cursor when the event occurred, if the event occurred on a mid-point on an editable polygon.

path.!doc: The index of the path beneath the cursor when the event occurred, if the event occurred on a vertex and the polygon is editable. Otherwise undefined.

vertex.!doc: The index of the vertex beneath the cursor when the event occurred, if the event occurred on a vertex and the polyline or polygon is editable. If the event does not occur on a vertex, the value is undefined.

clickable.!doc: Indicates whether this Polygon handles mouse events. Defaults to true.

draggable.!doc: If set to true, the user can drag this shape over the map. The geodesic property defines the mode of dragging. Defaults to false.

editable.!doc: If set to true, the user can edit this shape by dragging the control points shown at the vertices and on each segment. Defaults to false.

fillColor.!doc: The fill color. All CSS3 colors are supported except for extended named colors.

geodesic.!doc: When true, edges of the polygon are interpreted as geodesic and will follow the curvature of the Earth. When false, edges of the polygon are rendered as straight lines in screen space. Note that the shape of a geodesic polygon may appear to change when dragged, as the dimensions are maintained relative to the surface of the earth. Defaults to false.

map.!doc: Map on which to display Polygon.

paths.!doc: The ordered sequence of coordinates that designates a closed loop. Unlike polylines, a polygon may consist of one or more paths. As a result, the paths property may specify one or more arrays of LatLng coordinates. Paths are closed automatically; do not repeat the first vertex of the path as the last vertex. Simple polygons may be defined using a single array of LatLngs. More complex polygons may specify an array of arrays. Any simple arrays are converted into MVCArrays. Inserting or removing LatLngs from the MVCArray will automatically update the polygon on the map.

strokeColor.!doc: The stroke color. All CSS3 colors are supported except for extended named colors.

strokePosition.!doc: The stroke position. Defaults to CENTER. This property is not supported on Internet Explorer 8 and earlier.

visible.!doc: Whether this polygon is visible on the map. Defaults to true.

zIndex.!doc: The zIndex compared to other polys.

clickable.!doc: Indicates whether this Polyline handles mouse events. Defaults to true.

draggable.!doc: If set to true, the user can drag this shape over the map. The geodesic property defines the mode of dragging. Defaults to false.

editable.!doc: If set to true, the user can edit this shape by dragging the control points shown at the vertices and on each segment. Defaults to false.

geodesic.!doc: When true, edges of the polygon are interpreted as geodesic and will follow the curvature of the Earth. When false, edges of the polygon are rendered as straight lines in screen space. Note that the shape of a geodesic polygon may appear to change when dragged, as the dimensions are maintained relative to the surface of the earth. Defaults to false.

icons.!doc: The icons to be rendered along the polyline.

map.!doc: Map on which to display Polyline.

path.!doc: The ordered sequence of coordinates of the Polyline. This path may be specified using either a simple array of LatLngs, or an MVCArray of LatLngs. Note that if you pass a simple array, it will be converted to an MVCArray Inserting or removing LatLngs in the MVCArray will automatically update the polyline on the map.

strokeColor.!doc: The stroke color. All CSS3 colors are supported except for extended named colors.

visible.!doc: Whether this polyline is visible on the map. Defaults to true.

zIndex.!doc: The zIndex compared to other polys.

offset.!doc: The offset to the substring's start within the description string.
The offset, in unicode characters, of the start of this term in the description of the place.

value.!doc: The value of this term, e.g. "Taco Bell".

fromLatLngToPoint.!doc: Translates from the LatLng cylinder to the Point plane. This interface specifies a function which implements translation from given LatLng values to world coordinates on the map projection. The Maps API calls this method when it needs to plot locations on screen. Projection objects must implement this method.

fromPointToLatLng.!doc: This interface specifies a function which implements translation from world coordinates on a map projection to LatLng values. The Maps API calls this method when it needs to translate actions on screen to positions on the map. Projection objects must implement this method.

description.!doc: This is the unformatted version of the query suggested by the Places service.

matched_substrings.!doc: A set of substrings in the place's description that match elements in the user's input, suitable for use in highlighting those substrings. Each substring is identified by an offset and a length, expressed in unicode characters.

place_id.!doc: Only available if prediction is a place. A place ID that can be used to retrieve details about this place using the place details service (see  PlacesService.getDetails()).

terms.!doc: Information about individual terms in the above description. Categorical terms come first (e.g., "restaurant"). Address terms appear from most to least specific. For example, "San Francisco", and "CA".

bounds.!doc: Bounds for prediction biasing. Predictions will be biased towards, but not restricted to, the given bounds. Both location and radius will be ignored if bounds is set.

location.!doc: Location for prediction biasing. Predictions will be biased towards the given location and radius. Alternatively, bounds can be used.

offset.!doc: The character position in the input term at which the service uses text for predictions (the position of the cursor in the input field).

radius.!doc: The radius of the area used for prediction biasing. The radius is specified in meters, and must always be accompanied by a location property. Alternatively, bounds can be used.
